Definition.WordDefinition:
icky \icky\ adj. 1. very bad; repulsive; unpleasant; distasteful. [informal] [WordNet sense 1]
Syn: crappy, lousy, rotten, shitty, stinking, stinky. [WordNet 1.5]
2. sticky; as, icky, sticky goo. [WordNet sense 2]
Syn: gooey. [WordNet 1.5]
3. Overly sentimental; -- of stories or dramas. [PJC]
icky adj 1: very bad; "a lousy play"; "it's a stinking world" [syn: {crappy}, {lousy}, {rotten}, {shitty}, {stinking}, {stinky}] 2: soft and sticky [syn: {gooey}]
